&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Maintenance Technician is responsible for the day-to-day maintenance, repair, and operation of building systems and common areas within the shopping mall. This role ensures the property remains safe, functional, and visually appealing for tenants, customers, and staff by performing preventative maintenance, responding to service requests, and supporting building operations. #weshowup&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Building Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine inspections of building systems including HVAC, electrical, plumbing, lighting, and mechanical equipment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct preventative maintenance on facility equipment and infrastructure.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and repair building system issues.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repairs and General Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform general repairs including doors, locks, ceiling tiles, flooring, fixtures, and signage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Replace lamps,&amp;nbsp;ballasts, and lighting components in interior and exterior areas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform minor plumbing repairs including leaks, clogged drains, and fixture replacements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HVAC &amp;amp; Mechanical Support&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with HVAC maintenance including filter changes, belt replacements, and system inspections.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor building automation systems where applicable.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report&amp;nbsp;mechanical issues requiring specialized contractors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Safety &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with safety regulations and property management procedures.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist&amp;nbsp;with fire/life safety system inspections.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support emergency response procedures including power outages or system failures.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tenant Support&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to tenant maintenance requests&amp;nbsp;in a timely manner.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate access&amp;nbsp;for&amp;nbsp;vendors and contractors when&amp;nbsp;required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain positive working relationships with tenants.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exterior &amp;amp; Common Area Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain&amp;nbsp;common areas, restrooms, corridors, and service areas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist&amp;nbsp;with seasonal tasks such as snow preparation or storm response.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure walkways, parking areas, and entrances&amp;nbsp;remain&amp;nbsp;safe and clean.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete work orders and maintenance logs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
