&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our dedicated maintenance team at a midrise apartment community, where exceptional service and high-quality living standards are top priorities. We are seeking a skilled Maintenance Technician with experience in HVAC, plumbing, electrical, appliance repair, and general carpentry. This role requires a proactive problem-solver who can perform preventative maintenance and respond to work orders efficiently and professionally. A strong commitment to customer service, clear communication, and a polished, resident-first attitude are essential in maintaining our five-star living environment. #weshowup&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Class “A” customer service – building a good rapport with residents and going above and beyond whenever possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform repairs, maintenance, and cleaning of property both interior and exterior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Protect and assist in improving the value of the client’s assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform PM on unit based and building level equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform emergency on-call service in a rotation order&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform electrical, plumbing, carpentry, masonry and painting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repair and treat structures such as showers, sinks, appliances, doors/cabinets, walls and building exteriors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make ready units for new move-ins&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete grounds work such as grounds pick up, sweeping and light landscaping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma/GED required; equivalent experience will be considered in lieu of the education requirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintenance Technician for a minimum of 1 year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CFC Universal Certification preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of HVAC, electrical, and plumbing systems required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Class A experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office, particularly Outlook required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building automation systems experience a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Yardi experience a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current driver&#39;s license without major violations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outgoing personality with ability to relate to diverse group of people and build strong relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to respond to others’ needs in a timely and courteous manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work after hours and weekends, as needed including on-call rotation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to arrive at property location within 45 minutes to respond to emergencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be highly credible and trustworthy, and operate with high degree of integrity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must hold oneself and others accountable and strive for a high level of excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a positive, can-do attitude and be able to fuel growth and innovation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be customer-focused and results-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must want to continuously learn and develop&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional oral and written communication, active listening, and organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to establish strong working relationships with others in team setting&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
